pr_body:
Fixes #3758 

#### Describe the changes you have made in this PR -
- [x] Add Rubby debugger `debug` gem & update scripts to enable debugger at runtime
- [x] Add configuration for debugging with VSCode
- [x] Add configuration for debugging with Chrome
- [x] Modiy docker configuration to support remote debugging
- [x] Add configuration for remote debugging with VSCode in docker based installation
- [x] Update documentation

### Screenshots of the changes (If any) -

#### Working of Ruby Debugger

**Debugging With VSCode [local Installation]**

https://github.com/CircuitVerse/CircuitVerse/assets/57363826/1c0e957e-3eed-4555-8670-27df282786ab

**Debugging With Chrome [local installation]**

https://github.com/CircuitVerse/CircuitVerse/assets/57363826/0d7e8313-602e-4a79-a127-8fae572da82f


**Debugging With VSCode [docker based Installation]**

https://github.com/CircuitVerse/CircuitVerse/assets/57363826/2fad0794-35a3-40f5-b863-f934a1cdab05



Note: Please check **Allow edits from maintainers.** if you would like us to assist in the PR.

It's the latest version. 
Will remove if required", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 6, 2, 8, 53, 19, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'tanmoysrt', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1214113742, 'comment_body': "It's part of the bash script customized for the purpose of choosing chrome based debugger

- If we run `./bin/dev` that will run solargraph and we can connect from vscode or other supported IDE
  -  in this case that will use `Procfile.dev`
- If we run `./bin/dev chrome_debug` that will open up chrome for debugging.
  - In this case that will use `Procfile.chrome.dev`

To just choosing, which Procfile should be use `chrome_debug` flag has been added

---

We can use environment variable also, but it may be little bit more convenient for end-user to pass the choice from command line.
", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 6, 2, 8, 59, 8, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'tanmoysrt', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1214116312, 'comment_body': 'Sure

pr_body:
Fixes #3792

#### Describe the changes you have made in this PR -
- In rbs configuration, marked `meta-tags` to ignore, so that the rbs of meta-tags don't raise any issue
- In `sig/vendor`, added modified `rbs` of `meta-tags` gem to process it with `steep check`
- Added `steep check` in CI

For resolving the `RBS::DuplicatedMethodDefinitionError` issue for conflicting rbs definition , the maintainer of steep suggests to ignore `meta-tags` from rbs check and store modified `rbs` in sig folder for steep check.
Dicussion Thread - [ruby/rbs:1359](https://github.com/ruby/rbs/issues/1359)

Note: Please check **Allow edits from maintainers.** if you would like us to assist in the PR.

pr_body:
#### Describe the changes you have made in this PR -
- when user is a primary mentor
   - delete assignment
   - is able to edit assignment when assignment is not closed 
   -  is not able to edit assignment when assignment is closed
   - is able to close assignment
   - is able to reopen assignment
- when user is mentor
    - delete assignment
    - creates assignment
    - does not create assignment when name is blank
    - is able to edit assignment when assignment is not closed
    - is not able to edit assignment when assignment is close
    - is not able to close assignment
    - is able to reopen assignment

pr_body:
#### Describe the changes you have made in this PR -
1.  Added Redis APT Repository to `.gitpod.Dockerfile` to use the latest redis version always
2. Update extensions of `gitpod.yml` to use [open-vsx registry](https://open-vsx.org/) as Microsoft Terms & Policy does not allow to use their marketplace to fetch extensions outside of official VSCode. [Detailed about this issue](https://www.gitpod.io/blog/open-vsx)
3. Added VSIX files for `ruby-rubocop-revived` and `vscode-rdbg` as these two extensions are not published yet in [open-vsx registry](https://open-vsx.org/)
4. Added vscode settings for use `rvm` as package manager [required by ruby debugger extension]

#### Overall Imporvement
1. Gitpod is fixed [previously failed due to lower version of redis]
2. Gitpod extensions are working
3. Ruby debugger working fine
4. Solargraph extension is working fine



Note: Please check **Allow edits from maintainers.** if you would like us to assist in the PR.

pr_body:
Fixes #3914 

#### Describe the changes you have made in this PR -

- Dockerfile to serve as an environment [Like another remote development platform]
- Run the application with a non-root user with the same uid and gid as the host machine to resolve any Permission related issue. Also, the non-root user has been given passwordless sudo access to use if required,
- Persist PostgreSQL data using named volume
- Persist ruby bundle data using named volume
- Run setup scripts after the container become ready
- Move to foreman to have an identical setup
- The developer can restart the web service without restarting the container
- Provide bash access to the developer to interact as a regular os terminal
- Ruby debugger, Vite, Solargraph, and Siidekiq is working fine with the current setup
- The developer can do both unit testing and integration testing inside the docker environment

---

Run `bin/docker_run` to start the app in docker `[Linux & Mac]`
Run `bin/docker_run.ps1` to start in `Windows`

---

- [x] workflow updated

pr_title: feat: vite in docker dev environment and support root user
pr_body:
#### Describe the changes you have made in this PR -
- Added `vite` dev server in `web` container
  -  This can't be in a seperate container. Most probably rails locally check for vite dev server . If it does not found any process on port 3036 it build and serve the content. So vite in a seperate container will not work as the network namespace is not shared between containers.
- Added support to run docker setup as a root user [in case the linux system does not have a non-root user or docker rootless setup has not performed in the linux machine]

Note: Please check **Allow edits from maintainers.** if you would like us to assist in the PR.
